    "long_instructions": "# Do This\r\n1. Create three functions called `collect_paint`, `navigate_to_new_location`, and `paint_a_path`.\r\n#\r\n2. `collect_paint` should use a `while painter.is_on_bucket` loop to collect all the paint from a bucket.\r\n#\r\n3. `navigate_to_new_location` should use a `while painter.can_move` loop to move to a new location in the Neighborhood.\r\n#\r\n4. `paint_a_path` should use the `paint()` and `move()` methods to paint a path of a set length.\r\n#\r\n5. Use all three functions together to navigate and paint throughout the Neighborhood.\r\n    - Hint: Remember to use the `turn_left()` and `turn_right()` functions as needed.\r\n    \r\n6. Run your code and observe how the Painter collects paint, navigates to a new spot, and paints a path.\r\n",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n\nnatalia = Painter()\n\n# Create a new function take_paint that collects paint when the painter is on a bucket\ndef take_paint():\n\n# Create a new function can_move that navigates the painter to a new spot\ndef navigate_to_new_location():\n  \n# Create a new function paint_a_path that allows the painter to paint a set path\ndef paint_a_path():\n\n \n# Move through the Neighborhood using all three functions ",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
